
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "AsiaDestinations";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

@section Styles {
    <link href="~/Content/popular_destinations.css" rel="stylesheet" />
}

<div class="region-section">
    <div class="region-header">
        <h2>Discover Popular Destinations in Asia</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="destination-blog">

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/burj khalifa.png');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Dubai, UAE</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Burj Khalifa</h3>
                <p>The world's tallest building at 828 meters. The observation deck on the 124th floor offers unparalleled views of Dubai's impressive skyline and the Arabian Gulf.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/sensoji-temple-asakusa-tokyo.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Tokyo, Japan</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Senso-ji Temple</h3>
                <p>Tokyo's oldest and most significant temple, founded in 645 AD. The massive red lantern at the entrance and traditional architecture provide a peaceful escape from the bustling city.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Gardens by the Bay.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Singapore</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Gardens by the Bay</h3>
                <p>Futuristic Supertree structures tower up to 50 meters high in this stunning nature park. The evening light show transforms the gardens into a magical wonderland.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/taj mahal.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Agra, India</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Taj Mahal</h3>
                <p>This white marble mausoleum is a symbol of eternal love, built by Emperor Shah Jahan. The intricate architecture and perfect symmetry make it one of the world's most beautiful buildings.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Gyeongbokgung.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Seoul, South Korea</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Gyeongbokgung Palace</h3>
                <p>Established in 1395, it was the first royal palace of the Joseon dynasty, and is now one of the most significant tourist attractions in the country. </p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Great Wall of China.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Beijing, China</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Great Wall of China</h3>
                <p>The Great Wall of China is a series of fortifications in China. Built across the historical northern borders of ancient Chinese states and Imperial China as protection against various nomadic groups from the Eurasian Steppe.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/Grand palace bangkok.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Bangkok, Thailand</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Grand Palace</h3>
                <p>The Grand Palace is a complex of buildings at the heart of Bangkok, Thailand. The palace has been the official residence of the Kings of Siam since 1782.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/tian tan buddha.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Lantau Island, Hong Kong</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Tian Tan Buddha</h3>
                <p>The Big Buddha is a large bronze sculpture of Buddha, completed in 1993, and located at Ngong Ping, near Po Lin Monastery on Lantau Island, Hong Kong.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/borobudur temple.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Jawa Tengah, Indonesia</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Borobudur Temple</h3>
                <p>Borobudur, also transcribed Barabudur, is a 9th-century Mahayana Buddhist temple in Magelang Regency, near the town of Muntilan, northwest of the city of Yogyakarta, in Central Java, Indonesia.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/batu caves.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Selangor, Malaysia</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Batu Caves</h3>
                <p>Batu Caves is a 325-m tall mogote with a series of limestone caves in Gombak, Selangor, Malaysia. It is located about 13 km north of the capital city of Kuala Lumpur. The cave complex contains many Hindu temples, the most popular of which is a shrine dedicated to the deity Murugan.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/van mieu.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Hanoi, Vietnam</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Van Mieu</h3>
                <p>Van Mieu, literally translated as Temple of Literature, is a temple dedicated to Confucius in Hanoi, northern Vietnam. The temple was founded and first built in 1070 at the time of Emperor Lý Thánh Tông, and it hosted the Imperial Academy, Vietnam's first national university, from 1076 to 1779.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-image" style="background-image: url('../Images/angkor wat.jpg');">
                <div class="image-overlay">
                    <span class="location-tag">📍 Siem Reap, Cambodia</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="blog-content">
                <h3>Angkor Wat</h3>
                <p>Angkor Wat is a Hindu-Buddhist complex in Cambodia. Located on a site measuring 162.6 hectares within the ancient Khmer capital city of Angkor, it was originally constructed in 1150 CE as a Hindu temple dedicated to the deity Vishnu.</p>
                <div class="blog-tags">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>

